    "body": ">  there isn't a current account that we can set as from.\r\n\r\nThanks for your response, but why not set it to the zero address by default?\r\nFor `pure` functions that can work (since the `msg.sender` field can't be used by them)\r\nFor `view` functions - maybe you can give a warning to the user or something, but for many functions `msg.sender` field isn't used, and even when it is used - the user is well aware that he has no accounts connected.\r\n\r\n\r\nAnyways, if you choose to leave it the way it is, I think it'd be better to catch this error and give the user a better explanation about what's going on and possibly also suggest him the solution you mentioned.",
